  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CFGGoogleGraph
    From a CFGTree, constructs a URL for use in Google Charts
    CFGProductionRule
    CFG production rules are of the form:
    NODE1 :- NODE2, ..., NODEn
    where NODE1 is the only node on the left hand side of the production and there are n nodes on the right hand side of the production.
    In this program, n is >= 1, but has no upper constraint.
    CFGTree
    Represents a syntax tree corresponding a Sentence's cfg parse.
    CFGTreeNode
    A node in a CFGTree.
    ContextFreeGrammar
    An array list containing all CFG production rules for a given corpus
    CFG production rules are of the form:
    NODE1 :- NODE2, ..., NODEn
    where NODE1 is the only node on the left hand side of the production and there are n nodes on the right hand side of the production.
    In this program, n is >= 1, but has no upper constraint.
    Corpus
    A corpus object contains a list of Sentences and the grammars derived from those Sentences.
    DependencyGrammar
    A collection of DGGraphs
    DGGoogleGraph
    From a DGTree, constructs a URL for use in Google Charts
    NOTE: This particular chart type, GraphViz digraphs is deprecated by Google
    DGGraph
    DependencyGrammarGraph represents a single DG graph corresponding to a single sentence.
    DGNode
    A node in a DGraph
    DGRule
    A DGRule is a representation of the semantic relationship between two words, in which the relationship is specified by the edge label of a directed edge connecting two nodes which represent the two words.
    GoogleGraph<T>
    Abstract superclass for subclasses which take some sort of graph structure and create a URL for use in Google Charts.
